.Dd May 17, 1997
.Dt TRUST 3
.Os PGPlib
.Sh NAME
.Nm trust
.Nd routines to manipulate trust bytes
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Fd #include <pgplib.h>
.Ft int
.Fn trust2buf "PGPuserid_t *uid" "u_char **buf"
.Ft int
.Fn buf2trust "u_char *buf" "int len" "PGPuserid_t *uid"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
These routines manipulate trust-byte packages.
.Fn trust2buf
and
.Fn buf2trust
operate on a package compatible with RFC1991 that store a trust byte
in a keyring.
.Pp
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Upon success 0 is returned.  If an error occures, -1 is returned.
.Fn buf2trust
will return 1 if there is a synax error in the input.
.Pp
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr malloc 3
.Xr free 3
.Xr get_packetlen 3
.Xr PGPlib 3
.Pp
.Sh STANDARDS
The packet generated by
.Fn trust2buf 
is compatible with the format described in RFC1991.
.Pp
